# Normalize every text file to LF in the working tree on every platform. The build
# bakes multi-line template literals from src/ straight into dist/, so if src/ is
# checked out as CRLF (core.autocrlf=true on Windows) tsc emits CRLF *inside* those
# literals and the committed dist/ stops being byte-reproducible across OSes. Forcing
# eol=lf makes `npm run build` byte-identical on Windows, Linux, and macOS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# dist/ is the committed, shipped artifact and CI runs a strict `git diff
# --exit-code dist/`. Pin it to raw bytes (no EOL conversion) so the barrier is an
# honest byte-for-byte reproducibility check. With src/ forced to LF above, the build
# now emits LF dist/ on every OS, so the committed LF bytes match everywhere.
# (Realignment §2.0)
dist/** -text
